result.execSummary:
The defendant Logan D. Spencer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Threats to Injure/Accuse of Crime [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Repeater, Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.30(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Court calls @ 10:37 AM/ RM 301, 21CF129 & 22CF153. Defendant Logan D. Spencer in court, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Attorney John Zich in court for Logan D. Spencer.  Attorney Kelly L Hays in court for State of Wisconsin. State gives sentencing remarks and recites terms of agreement in 21CF129, Def. to plea Guilty or No Contest to Ct. 2, joint recommendation, Court to impose and stay 9 months jail sentence to run concurrent to 22CF153 Ct. 1 and Ct. 3, but consecutive to any other sentence, 2 years probation, Def. to pay court costs with conditions to complete AODA assessment in treatment, Maintain Absolute Sobriety, Complete domestic violence assessment in treatment, Complete metal health assessment, No dangerous weapons, No violent contact with victim or victims family, Complete family counselling, obtain and maintain full time work and complete any other counselling as deemed necessary by agent. Ct. 1 to be dismissed and read in. In 22CF153, Def. to plea Guilty or No Contest to Ct. 1, joint recommendation, Court to impose and stay 4 year sentence, 2 years initial confinement, 2 years extended supervision concurrent to Ct. 3 in 21CF129 consecutive with any other sentence, 4 years probation, Def. to pay court costs and comply with any other conditions previously stated. Ct. 2, Amend charge to Misdemeanor bail jumping, as a repeater, Def. to plea Guilty or No Contest, Joint recommendation, 4 months jail consecutive to any other sentence, Def. to pay court costs. Ct. 3, amend charge to disorderly domestic abuse as standard repeater. Imposed and stayed 2 years sentence, 1 year initial confinement, 1 year extended supervision concurrent to Ct. 1 in 21CF129, consecutive to any other sentence, 2 years probation, Def. to pay court costs and conditions to be same as previously stated. Court questions agreement, State responds. Atty Zich is in agreeance. Def. is also in agreeance and wishes to accept agreement. Atty Zich has filed waiver and information. State will file amended information. Court reviews plea questionnaire and waiver of rights with Def. In 21CF129, Def. pleas No Contest to Ct. 2. In 22CF153 Def. pleas to Ct. 1 Guilty, Ct. 2 (being amended) Def. pleas Guilty, Ct. 3 (being amended) Def. pleas Guilty. Court grants States motion to dismiss and read in Ct. 1 in 21CF129. Court reviews Def. constitutional rights and all potential penalties, charges and elements. Atty Zich has reviewed plea questionnaire and waiver of rights with Def. and is satisfied. Court finds Def. has freely and voluntarily entered into plea agreement. Court has reviewed criminal complaints and finds adequate and factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds Def. Guilty in 21CF129, Ct 2. In 22CF153, Court finds Def. Guilty on Ct. 1, Ct. 2 and Ct. 3. State notes victim has filed a letter and wishes to use as victim impact statement. State requests Court to adopt joint recommendation. Court goes off record. Court goes back on record, 11:05AM. Atty Zich makes sentencing remarks and requests Court accept joint recommendation. Def. makes sentencing remarks. Court considers sentencing factors and grants joint recommendation. Court orders on 21CF129 Ct. 2, imposed and stayed 9 months county jail sentence with huber privileges concurrent with Ct. 1 and Ct. 3 in 22CF153, but consecutive to any other sentences ordered today or already ordered. Probation 2 years, Def. to pay court costs to include a $200 DNA surcharge and provide sample with conditions to complete AODA assessment and follow through, Maintain Absolute Sobriety, complete domestic violence assessment and follow through with recommendations, complete mental health evaluation and follow through with recommendations, Def. not to possess any dangerous weapons, No violent or abusive contact with victims identified in this case or their families,  Def. to participate in family counselling, Maintain full time employment, participate in any other counselling as deemed fit by agent. 22CF153 Ct. 1 imposed and stayed 4 years prison, 2 years initial confinement, 2 years extended supervision concurrent to 21CF129, consecutive to Ct. 2 and any other sentences already received, probation 4 years, Def. to pay court costs to include a $250 DNA surcharge and same conditions as previously ordered. Ct. 2, 4 months in county jail with huber privileges consecutive to any other sentence ordered today or previously ordered. Def. to pay court costs to include a $200 DNA surcharge. Ct. 3 imposed and stayed 2 years prison, 1 year initial confinement, 1 year extended supervision concurrent to Ct. 1 and Ct. 2 in 21CF129, consecutive to any other sentence ordered today or have already been ordered to serve, 2 years probation. Def. to pay court costs to include a $200 DNA surcharge and all other same conditions as previously ordered. Court questions credit. On 21CF153 Def. has 40 days credit. On 21CF129 Def. has 14 days credit. Atty Zich is in agreeance. Court grants 40 days credit on 21CF153, can be applied on Ct. 2. 21CF129, 14 days credit if revoked. Court questions if Def. is eligible for programming. State responds. Atty Zich responds. Def. advised of firearms and voting rights. If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. $500 cash bond to retire court costs on Ct. 2 in 21CF129, any amount left over to be refunded to poster. Any additional amount due to be paid during probation. 22CF153, no cash posted, court costs to be paid during probation. Ct. 2 Def. will have to enter payment plan, unless paid today. Payment plan on Ct. 2 to start 90 days from today. State advises Def. is eligible for challenge incarceration and earned release on 22CF153. Court advises Def. of right to appeal.

2:11 PM/Rm. 301/Defendant Logan D. Spencer not in court.  Prosecuting attorney Elizabeth R. Gebert in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter by Zoom.  State moves Court to modify no contact provision of bond to 'No contact with victim and victim's residence except via recorded phone or video calls.'  Court so orders.  Copy of minutes to go to Sheriff's Dept.  Recess 2:14 p.m. (copy of minutes given to LCSD)

1:16 PM/Room 203.  Defendant Logan D. Spencer appeared by video, in custody at Langlade County Jail.  Attorney John Zich in court for Logan D. Spencer.  Attorney Kelly L Hays in court for State of Wisconsin. All appearances are by Zoom. Def. advised of his right to appear in person. Def. agreeable to appearing by Zoom. State asks that Court find that counts are transactionally related. The Court finds that counts are transactionally related. Dep. Travis Krueger, duly sworn on oath, testifies. State rests. Witness excused. No further testimony. The Court finds there is probable cause, binds over for further proceedings. State ready to proceed to arraignment. State has e-filed Information and emailed to Attny Zich. Count 2 has been corrected in Information. Court confirms change of possible penalty for Count 2. Attny Zich acknowledges receipt, waives reading, reserves jurisdictional objections and enters pleas of not guilty. Court receives pleas of not guilty. State indicates  case set Sept. 29 at 10:30 a.m. for tentative plea and sentencing. Discussion as to bail modification hearings and which court official they can be in front of.  CC does not believe he has authority to amend bond. State has complied with victim rights.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 29, 2022 at 10:30 am.

1:25 PM Defendant Logan D. Spencer appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Kelly L Hays in court for State of Wisconsin. Def. has copy of complaint, advised of charges and penalties.  Def. given atty rights and given 4 options, PD, hire own or court appointed atty or represent himself.  Def. will contact PD. & court orders. Court heard on Ct 2 maximum in prison. State gives bail/bond recommendation with conditions no contact with victim or residence, Maintain Absolute Sobriety. No illegal use or possession of controlled substances, No possession of dangerous weapons.  Atty Zich now appears via zoom and represents def on a different matter.  Atty Zich heard on bail/bond recommendation. CC makes statement to victim. Court gives factors in setting bond & orders $5000 cash bond with conditions No contact with victim or victim residence, Maintain Absolute Sobriety. No possession of controlled substances without valid prescription, No possession of dangerous weapons.   Atty Zich will not waive time limits for p.h.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 30, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
